Interface SimpleQueue<E>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayQueue

    public interface SimpleQueue<E>

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isEmpty()
      Returns true if the queue is empty (there are no elements in it), false if it has at least one element.
      boolean offer(E e)
      Tries to put the given element at the tail of this queue, returning true if successful, false otherwise.
      E peek()
      Returns the element at the head of this queue, without removing it.
      E poll()
      Returns the element at the head of this queue, removing it.
      int size()
      Returns the number of elements in this queue.
